REGION:
Forest of Allanar (FA)
TYPE: Dense magical forest
AREA: 200 sq mi
CENTER: Aeressari (around ancient tree)

HISTORY:
Elven Kingdom of Allanar fell to civil war

FEATURES:
Overgrown ruins, moss, fey, treants, dryad groves

POPULATION (CANONICAL DISTRIBUTION):
High Elf 25%
Wood Elf 25%
Sea Elf 10%
Eladrin 10%
Drow 10%
Other 20% (Forest Gnome, Human, Aasimar, Centaur)

────────────────────────────────
SETTLEMENTS (CLOSED; EXHAUSTIVE; COORDINATES CANONICAL)
────────────────────────────────

Metropolis:
- Aeressari [Aere] (162,176)
  DESC: Living elven metropolis grown from ancient tree and living stone;
        political, religious, and magical center of FA

City:
- Cerallya (135,198)
  DESC: Ancient wood elf city once hidden by enchantment;
        cultural, musical, and spiritual hub seeking restoration

Towns:
- Andizyre (154,219)
  DESC: Beast-hunter town; monster slaying, parts trade, frontier defense
- Stormwood [Smoo] (206,165)
  DESC: Storm-battered trade port near northern mountains;
        wind, sea traffic, hardened infrastructure
- Strauvani (176,81)
  DESC: Trade route stop; inns, stables, caravan services

Villages:
- Oakwood [Oak] (87,99)
  DESC: Human logging village under strict lumber treaty;
        elven oversight and racial tension
- Esalym (195,147)
  DESC: Small forest village; subsistence living, minimal external influence
- Teafield (104,150)
  DESC: Agrarian village; tea cultivation, quiet trade stop,
        low political importance

INVARIANT:
Any settlement not listed above DOES NOT EXIST in the Forest of Allanar.

